            <thetext>It seems that qx.bom.element.Decoration is abused to function as a generalized 
background image handler. E.g. qx.html.Image, through its .setSource() method, 
calls qx.bom.element.Decoration.update(), to set source URI, positioning and 
such. This is misleading, as these are generic features that are not confined 
to decorations.

The generic functionality should either be extracted in an suitable class 
(qx.bom.element.Background or qx.bom.element.BackgroundImage), and then just be 
used in qx.bom.element.Decoration. Or, if this is the sole functionality of 
qx.bom.element.Decoration, the class be renamed accordingly.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
